cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a new method for attributed graph learning using graph convolutional neural networks. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of 2-D graph convolution suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on node classification and clustering tasks, which are common in natural language processing (cs.CL) and social network analysis (cs.SI).
